WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.366
The FX original series,
The Americans.

00:03.400 --> 00:05.698
The new season,
Wednesdays at 10:00 on FX.

00:07.400 --> 00:09.061
PREVIOUSLY ON
"THE AMERICANS"...

00:09.110 --> 00:11.169
LAST YEAR, THE CENTRE STARTED
A PROGRAM TO DEVELOP OFFICERS

00:11.210 --> 00:13.303
THEY'RE CALLING
SECOND-GENERATION ILLEGALS.

00:13.340 --> 00:15.706
THE CENTRE --
THEY WANT PAIGE TO BE NEXT.

00:15.740 --> 00:17.571
IT WOULD DESTROY HER.

00:17.610 --> 00:19.146
TO BE LIKE US?

00:19.180 --> 00:22.843
THAT'S EVERYONE
WORKING ON AFGHANISTAN.

00:22.890 --> 00:25.518
EXCUSE ME. MA'AM?
WE'RE WITH THE FBI --

00:25.550 --> 00:27.313
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

00:27.360 --> 00:29.851
I HAD A LIST OF NAMES
IN MY POCKET.

00:29.890 --> 00:30.857
WE'LL GET IN.

00:30.890 --> 00:32.858
SWEDISH INTELLIGENCE
NEEDS YOU.

00:34.730 --> 00:35.890
[ GASPING ]

00:35.930 --> 00:37.727
Philip:
THIS IS A TERRIBLE THING.

00:37.770 --> 00:39.431
BUT I CAN HELP YOU.

00:39.470 --> 00:41.097
I CAN MAKE THIS GO AWAY.

00:41.140 --> 00:43.665
Brooks: WE GOT INTELLIGENCE
FROM THE CIA THIS MORNING.

00:43.710 --> 00:45.109
THEY CONVICTED
NINA KRILOVA.

00:45.140 --> 00:47.279
ESPIONAGE AND TREASON.

00:57.390 --> 00:58.516
[ LOCK DISENGAGES ]

00:58.550 --> 01:02.281
[ CELL DOOR CREAKS ]

01:04.890 --> 01:06.892
[ ELECTRICITY HUMMING ]

01:16.570 --> 01:18.561
[ URINATING ]

01:23.480 --> 01:25.641
[ URINATING STOPS ]

02:10.130 --> 02:12.018
LET'S GO.

02:24.970 --> 02:28.531
I HAVE TO MAKE A PHONE CALL TO
HELP GET THINGS TAKEN CARE OF.

02:28.580 --> 02:30.207
[ GLASS CLINKS ]

02:30.250 --> 02:32.946
YOUSAF, AS LONG AS YOU LET ME DO
WHAT I DO,

02:32.980 --> 02:34.140
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

02:34.180 --> 02:36.148
[ CAP POPS ]
OKAY?

02:36.190 --> 02:38.488
I'LL BE BACK
IN 10 MINUTES.

02:41.820 --> 02:44.550
[ SIGHS ]

02:47.000 --> 02:49.150
[ KEYS JINGLING ]

02:51.430 --> 02:52.499
UP LATE.

02:52.540 --> 02:53.666
ALGEBRA.

02:53.700 --> 02:55.395
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

02:55.440 --> 02:56.964
WHERE'S DAD?

02:57.010 --> 02:59.205
HAD TO GO
BACK TO THE OFFICE.

03:00.540 --> 03:02.974
UH, CAN YOU DROP US OFF
IN CLARENDON TOMORROW NIGHT?

03:03.010 --> 03:05.501
WE WANT TO HAND OUT
THE FIRST 1,500 FLIERS.

03:05.550 --> 03:07.711
UM...YEAH, SURE.

03:12.090 --> 03:13.216
OH!

03:13.260 --> 03:15.216
YOU OKAY?
YEAH.

03:15.260 --> 03:17.581
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

03:21.460 --> 03:22.825
HELLO?

03:22.870 --> 03:24.929
HEY, HONEY.
IS, UH, IS MOM THERE?

03:24.970 --> 03:26.494
Yeah.
Hold on a sec.

03:26.540 --> 03:27.564
IT'S DAD.

03:33.110 --> 03:34.338
HI.

03:34.380 --> 03:36.905
MORE...WORK HERE
THAN I ANTICIPATED.

03:36.950 --> 03:40.215
UM...I HAVE
A LOT OF FILES TO MOVE.

03:40.250 --> 03:42.718
I'm -- I'm really sorry.
I could use some help.

03:42.750 --> 03:44.615
NO PROBLEM.
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

03:47.390 --> 03:49.779
HEN RY'S ASLEEP, RIGHT?

03:49.830 --> 03:51.388
YEP.

03:51.430 --> 03:52.920
HEY, MOM.

03:52.960 --> 03:54.257
YEAH?

03:54.300 --> 03:56.564
HAVE YOU EVER CALLED DAD
AT THE OFFICE AT NIGHT

03:56.600 --> 03:58.067
AND HE DIDN'T ANSWER?

03:58.100 --> 04:00.762
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

04:00.800 --> 04:03.234
I DON'T KNOW -- MY FRIEND NANCY
WAS JUST TELLING ME

04:03.270 --> 04:05.602
HOW HER DAD KEPT SAYING
HE WAS WORKING LATE NIGHTS,

04:05.640 --> 04:08.108
BUT THEN ONE NIGHT,
HER MOM WENT DOWN TO THE OFFICE,

04:08.140 --> 04:09.641
AND HE WASN'T THERE.

04:09.680 --> 04:11.443
WHERE WAS HE?

04:11.480 --> 04:13.448
WITH HIS SECRETARY.

04:13.480 --> 04:16.074
JUST...
NOT AT THE OFFICE.

04:16.120 --> 04:18.281
MM.

04:18.320 --> 04:21.619
YEAH, I GUESS I DON'T
THINK ABOUT THAT TOO MUCH.

04:21.660 --> 04:24.356
I MEAN,
YOU'VE SEEN BARB.

04:26.190 --> 04:28.556
PAIGE, DON'T WORRY.

04:28.600 --> 04:31.091
YOUR FATHER
IS NOT HAVING AN AFFAIR.

04:31.130 --> 04:33.633
HE'S GONE A LOT AT NIGHT.

04:33.670 --> 04:35.297
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

04:38.270 --> 04:39.635
I JUST KNOW.

04:43.450 --> 04:45.247
[ SMOOCHES ]

04:45.280 --> 04:48.272
YOU GUYS LOOK OUT
FOR EACH OTHER -- YOU AND DAD.

04:48.320 --> 04:50.447
YEAH, OF COURSE.

04:50.490 --> 04:52.185
MORE THAN US.

04:53.660 --> 04:55.651
PAIGE, THAT --
NO, THAT'S --

04:55.690 --> 04:56.952
NO, IT'S OKAY.

04:56.990 --> 04:59.959
I'M -- I'M GLAD
THAT YOU GUYS ARE...

05:00.000 --> 05:01.649
IT'S A GOOD THING.

05:08.840 --> 05:10.705
I'LL BE HOME SOON.

05:48.440 --> 05:50.749
YOU DON'T WANT TO ATTRACT
ATTENTION BY BEING SILENT.

05:50.780 --> 05:52.145
IF PEOPLE
ARE TALKING ABOUT

05:52.180 --> 05:54.148
THE WIFE OF A PENTAGON OFFICIAL
GONE MISSING,

05:54.180 --> 05:56.341
DON'T PRETEND
YOU HAVEN'T HEARD ABOUT IT.

05:56.390 --> 05:58.517
BUT BY MONDAY,
THIS SHOULD BE QUIET.

06:01.090 --> 06:03.729
[ SIGHS ]

06:05.060 --> 06:06.084
WHO ARE YOU?

06:10.900 --> 06:14.267
MY PEOPLE ARE DYING
IN AFGHANISTAN.

06:14.300 --> 06:16.632
[ SIGHS ]

06:44.270 --> 06:45.919
NICE AND EASY.

06:49.610 --> 06:51.100
[ BACKUP SIGNAL BEEPING ]

06:53.580 --> 06:56.504
[ DRILL WHIRRING ]

07:05.620 --> 07:07.679
[AIR HISSING ]

07:16.930 --> 07:19.160
[ LABORED BREATHING ]

07:26.310 --> 07:29.302
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

07:29.340 --> 07:32.343
[ LAUGHS ]

07:32.380 --> 07:35.178
WELCOME TO THE UNITED STATES
OF AMERICA, MA'AM.

08:21.360 --> 08:22.964
[ BONES SNAP ]

08:23.000 --> 08:25.821
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

08:31.370 --> 08:32.837
[ GRUNTS ]
[ BONES SNAP ]

08:32.880 --> 08:35.007
[ SIGHS ]

08:37.510 --> 08:40.013
HERE YOU GO.

08:40.050 --> 08:41.677
YEAH.

08:43.950 --> 08:45.838
[ BONES SNAP ]
[ GRUNTS ]

08:48.520 --> 08:50.852
HOLD IT DOWN THERE.

08:56.970 --> 08:58.028
[ BONES SNAP ]
[ GRUNTS ]

08:58.070 --> 08:59.321
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

08:59.370 --> 09:00.689
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

09:13.880 --> 09:16.849
[ METAL DOOR SLIDES ]

09:16.890 --> 09:18.289
[CLANK]

09:18.320 --> 09:20.379
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

09:23.090 --> 09:24.728
[ LOCK DISENGAGES ]

09:29.400 --> 09:32.028
[ LOCK ENGAGES ]

09:32.070 --> 09:33.890
[ FOOTSTEPS DEPART ]

09:36.910 --> 09:38.263
[CLANK]

09:42.750 --> 09:45.310
[Shakily] UM...

09:52.120 --> 09:53.587
ENGLISH?

09:56.320 --> 09:58.652
[ BREATH ES DEEPLY ]

09:58.690 --> 10:00.726
I'M EVI.

10:00.760 --> 10:02.762
FROM BELGIUM.

10:12.270 --> 10:13.828
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

10:16.340 --> 10:18.774
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

10:27.620 --> 10:29.781
[ CRYING, GASPING ]

10:40.500 --> 10:42.661
[ CRYING, GASPING
CONTINUE ]

10:52.650 --> 10:53.674
[ GRUNTS ]

11:16.170 --> 11:19.708
I REALLY SHOULDN'T
HANG AROUND HERE ANY LONGER.

11:19.740 --> 11:23.073
YOU THINK YOU CAN BE THERE
TOMORROW BY 3:00?

11:23.110 --> 11:25.874
THERE'S AN INDOOR POOL
AT THE BACK OF THE BUILDING.

11:29.520 --> 11:31.044
GOOD.

11:32.690 --> 11:36.182
[ DOOR OPENS ]

11:36.220 --> 11:38.188
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

11:38.230 --> 11:42.326
IT WAS SUPPOSED TO BE A ROOM
WITH NO ADJOINING ROOMS.

11:42.360 --> 11:44.396
I MADE THE RESERVATION
MYSELF.

11:46.740 --> 11:48.093
WELL, PLEASE CALL ME
WHEN IT'S READY.

11:48.140 --> 11:49.266
THANK YOU.

11:49.300 --> 11:50.904
THANK YOU.

11:53.540 --> 11:55.531
I'M SORRY -- IT'S GONNA BE
ANOTHER HOUR OR TWO

11:55.580 --> 11:56.672
BEFORE THE HOTEL'S READY.

11:56.710 --> 11:58.371
THEY'RE TRYING
TO RUSH IT.

11:58.410 --> 12:00.412
[ Russian accent]
I UNDERSTAND.

12:06.390 --> 12:08.210
WHAT IS THIS...

12:08.260 --> 12:10.785
UM...

12:10.830 --> 12:13.549
INSTITUTE YOU WORK AT?

12:15.730 --> 12:17.891
[ Muffled ]
THIS IS SO GOOD.

12:17.930 --> 12:19.420
OH.

12:19.470 --> 12:21.131
I'M GLAD YOU LIKE IT.

12:23.410 --> 12:25.628
IT'S THE INSTITUTE
IN MOSCOW,

12:25.670 --> 12:30.539
RESPONSIBLE FOR REPORTING
TO SOVIET LEADERSHIP

12:30.580 --> 12:35.279
ON ALL ASPECTS REGARDING
GEOPOLITICAL SIGNIFICANCE

12:35.320 --> 12:38.915
REGARDING UNITED STATES
AND CANADA.

12:42.420 --> 12:45.218
CAN I GET YOU
ANYTHING ELSE?

12:45.260 --> 12:47.251
NO. NOT NOW.

13:00.280 --> 13:02.737
YOU OKAY?

13:02.780 --> 13:04.839
I'M JUST TIRED.

13:07.220 --> 13:10.109
IT'S SO STRANGE...

13:10.150 --> 13:13.313
TO BE FINALLY HERE...

13:13.360 --> 13:15.612
THAT IT'S ALL OVER.

13:18.130 --> 13:20.792
IT'S NOT...REALLY OVER.

13:22.870 --> 13:24.497
NO.

13:39.010 --> 13:40.318
MOM.

13:41.580 --> 13:42.842
MOM.

13:51.390 --> 13:53.324
[ KNIFE THUDS]

14:03.370 --> 14:05.361
YOU OKAY?

14:09.540 --> 14:12.646
I WAS JUST THINKING
ABOUT THIS BLUE DRESS

14:12.680 --> 14:14.910
THAT MY MOTHER
USED TO HAVE.

14:26.760 --> 14:28.728
[ REPORTERS SHOUTING QUESTIONS ]

14:32.070 --> 14:34.595
EXCUSE ME.
WHY DID YOU DEFECT?

14:34.640 --> 14:36.596
UM...

14:36.640 --> 14:41.179
MY -- MY CONSCIENCE WOULD NOT
LET ME CONTINUE TO DO MY JOB,

14:41.210 --> 14:44.702
WHICH INCLUDED
TO SUPPORT SOVIET GOVERNMENT

14:44.750 --> 14:49.414
WHILE ITS ARMY WAS CREATING
SO MUCH SUFFERING

14:49.450 --> 14:51.884
FOR THE INNOCENT PEOPLE
OF AFGHANISTAN.

14:51.920 --> 14:55.617
CHILDREN AND WOMEN
ARE DYING EVERY DAY

14:55.660 --> 14:59.426
BECAUSE SOVIET LEADERSHIP
BELIEVES THAT THEY CAN DECIDE

14:59.460 --> 15:01.928
FOR THE FUTURE
OF ANOTHER COUNTRY.

15:01.960 --> 15:05.066
[ REPORTERS SHOUTING QUESTIONS ]

15:05.100 --> 15:07.091
DO YOU THINK
BREZHNEV'S DEATH

15:07.140 --> 15:10.598
COULD HAVE AN IMPACT ON
THE SOVIET WAR IN AFGHANISTAN?

15:14.610 --> 15:17.044
I CANNOT TELL THE FUTURE.

15:17.080 --> 15:22.438
HOWEVER, THE ENTIRE POLITBURO
IS BEHIND THIS TERRIBLE WAR.

15:22.480 --> 15:24.789
[ REPORTERS SHOUTING QUESTIONS ]

15:33.300 --> 15:35.359
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

16:07.300 --> 16:09.450
I SAW IT
ON THE NEWS.

16:09.500 --> 16:11.525
A "MISSING PERSON,"
THEY CALL IT HERE.

16:13.700 --> 16:17.158
SHE WAS...
REALLY SOMETHING.

16:17.210 --> 16:21.829
I MEAN,
SHE COULD BE A LITTLE...

16:21.880 --> 16:24.371
OUT OF HER HEAD ALMOST,

16:24.410 --> 16:28.949
BUT SHE W-WAS
REALLY SOMETHING.

16:28.980 --> 16:30.845
I THOUGHT SHE WAS
SUCH A SILLY LI'I'I'LE CREATURE

16:30.890 --> 16:32.141
WHEN I MET HER.

16:32.190 --> 16:35.057
BUT SHE HAD A DEGREE
IN ART HISTORY.

16:35.090 --> 16:36.455
SHE SPOKE FRENCH.

16:36.490 --> 16:39.254
I COULD TALK TO HER.

16:41.530 --> 16:43.919
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.
I JUST --

16:45.900 --> 16:47.367
[ SIGHS ]

16:47.400 --> 16:51.564
IT WAS UNFAIR,
THE POSITION YOU WERE PUT IN.

16:51.610 --> 16:54.101
THIS JOB...

16:56.080 --> 16:59.243
HOW LONG ARE YOU HERE?

16:59.280 --> 17:00.838
I'M NOT SURE YET.

17:00.880 --> 17:02.711
DO YOU HAVE MEETINGS?

17:04.450 --> 17:06.645
I NEED NAMES --

17:06.690 --> 17:09.409
PEOPLE WORKING
IN THE CIA'S AFGHAN GROUP.

17:11.590 --> 17:14.320
I KNOW SOME OF THEM,
BUT JUST THEIR FIRST NAMES.

17:14.360 --> 17:16.419
DO YOU THINK
YOU COULD ARRANGE A MEETING?

17:16.460 --> 17:20.260
YES, BUT I'VE ONLY MET THEM
BEFORE AT CIA HEADQUARTERS.

17:20.300 --> 17:24.168
TELL THEM YOU NEED
TO MEET THEM IN PRIVATE

17:24.210 --> 17:29.000
AND THAT YOU HAVE SOMETHING
YOU HAVE TO TELL THEM.

17:29.040 --> 17:31.144
DO YOU NEED IDEAS?

17:34.450 --> 17:36.611
I HAVE SOMETHING.

17:38.420 --> 17:41.457
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING,
SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

17:51.070 --> 17:53.493
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

17:55.570 --> 17:57.606
[ Russian accent]
YOU DIDN'T EXPECT THIS, DID YOU,

17:57.640 --> 18:02.532
THAT YOU'LL HAVE TO PAY
THE PRICE, TOO?

18:02.580 --> 18:04.798
ON YOUR KNEES.

18:07.980 --> 18:10.119
IT RUINS YOUR LIFE, TOO,
OLEG.

18:10.150 --> 18:12.243
I HAVE IMMUNITY.

18:12.290 --> 18:13.985
THEY'LL GET YOU FOR IT.

18:14.020 --> 18:15.089
YEAH?

18:15.120 --> 18:18.658
DID THEY GET YOU?

18:18.690 --> 18:20.999
AFTER YOU KILLED
VLAD KOSYGIN?

18:22.960 --> 18:24.791
SHE TOLD ME WHAT YOU DID.

18:24.830 --> 18:26.559
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

18:26.600 --> 18:30.468
AND YOU HAD HER SENT
TO A LABOR CAMP.

18:32.510 --> 18:35.104
I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'LL BELIEVE ME,

18:35.140 --> 18:36.505
BUT I DID LOVE HER.

18:36.540 --> 18:37.746
OH!

18:37.780 --> 18:39.179
SHUT UP.

18:39.210 --> 18:41.610
IF THERE'S ANYTHING
I CAN DO FOR HER...

18:41.650 --> 18:42.947
YOU'LL WHAT?

18:42.980 --> 18:45.915
STAN BEEMAN
FROM THE AMERICAN FBI

18:45.950 --> 18:47.611
IS GOING TO RESCUE

18:47.660 --> 18:50.879
A SOVIET TRAITOR
FROM A SOVIET PRISON?

18:52.190 --> 18:55.125
I DON'T KNOW
HOW YOUR GODDAMN SYSTEM WORKS.

18:55.160 --> 18:56.798
MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING.

18:56.830 --> 18:59.867
OH, YOU DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING.

18:59.900 --> 19:01.492
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

19:01.540 --> 19:03.508
[ GUN COCKS ]

19:05.510 --> 19:08.399
ON YOUR KNEES.

19:12.310 --> 19:14.642
SCREW YOU, OLEG.

19:14.680 --> 19:19.413
YOU WANT TO SHOOT ME...
SHOOT ME IN THE BACK.

19:20.660 --> 19:23.220
[ BREATHES SHAKILY ]

19:43.250 --> 19:45.775
[ CAR DOOR OPENS ]

19:51.250 --> 19:55.311
[ TOOTHBRUSH SCRAPING ]

19:55.360 --> 19:57.726
[ GROANS ]

19:57.760 --> 20:00.593
[ TOOTHBRUSH SCRAPES LIGHTLY ]

20:00.630 --> 20:01.619
[ SPITS ]

20:05.070 --> 20:08.892
WHO KNOWS
HOW MUCH SECURITY THEY'LL BRING?

20:08.940 --> 20:10.498
IF ANY.

20:10.540 --> 20:13.373
I MEAN, MAYBE THIS DOESN'T
RING ANY BELLS FOR THEM.

20:13.410 --> 20:16.379
OR THEY'RE COVERING
EVERYBODY IN THE AFGHAN GROUP

20:16.410 --> 20:18.901
BECAUSE THEY ALMOST LOST
A LIST OF THEM.

20:21.050 --> 20:23.280
I'D FEEL A LOT BETTER
WITH A LITTLE BIT OF A TEAM.

20:23.320 --> 20:25.049
HANS ISN'T READY YET.

20:25.090 --> 20:26.614
HOW LONG?

20:26.650 --> 20:28.413
COUPLE MONTHS, MAYBE.

20:28.460 --> 20:32.157
WELL, MAYBE YOU COULD PUSH
THINGS ALONG A LITTLE FASTER.

20:37.100 --> 20:38.965
YOU KNOW, WE WOULDN'T BE
IN THIS SITUATION

20:39.000 --> 20:40.888
IF I'D BEEN HANDLING YOUSAF
FROM THE START.

20:40.940 --> 20:43.033
PLEASE DON'T BLAME
WHAT HE DID TO ANNELISE ON ME

20:43.070 --> 20:44.867
BECAUSE YOU KNOW
THINGS LIKE THIS HAPPEN.

20:44.910 --> 20:46.229
THAT'S NOT
WHAT I WAS SAYING.

20:46.270 --> 20:48.204
IT IS UNPREDICT ABLE,
AND THAT IS EXACTLY WHY

20:48.240 --> 20:50.276
I DO NOT WANT PAIGE
EVER ENTERING INTO THIS.

20:50.310 --> 20:52.039
PHILIP --
I DON'T WANT HER
PUTTING PEOPLE INTO A SUITCASE,

20:52.080 --> 20:54.071
AND I DON'T WANT HER
ENDING UP IN A SUITCASE.

20:54.120 --> 20:55.815
DON'T YOU DARE.
I WOULD NEVER PUT HER
IN THIS POSITION.

20:55.850 --> 20:56.942
WHAT DO YOU THINK
WILL HAPPEN?

20:56.980 --> 20:58.789
WHAT DO YOU THINK
WILL HAPPEN?

20:58.820 --> 21:01.459
YOU THINK SHE'LL WORK
SOME CUSHY JOB FOR THE CIA,

21:01.490 --> 21:03.424
THE NSA FOR 20 YEARS,
NOTHING ELSE?

21:03.460 --> 21:05.052
WHY NOT?
THAT'S WHAT THEY NEED.

21:05.090 --> 21:07.888
UNTIL SOMETHING CHANGES.

21:07.930 --> 21:10.125
IT ALWAYS CHAN--
IT ALWAYS CHANGES.

21:10.160 --> 21:11.468
WHAT DO YOU WANT,
PHILIP --

21:11.500 --> 21:12.922
A GUARANTEE
THAT LIFE'S GONNA BE EASY?

21:12.970 --> 21:15.632
FOR MY DAUGHTER?

21:15.670 --> 21:17.638
YEAH.

21:24.150 --> 21:25.344
[ SIGHS ]

21:31.620 --> 21:33.508
[ Ringing ]

21:33.560 --> 21:35.312
Hi. This is Arthur.

21:35.360 --> 21:37.328
If you have a message
for me, Sandra, or Matthew,

21:37.360 --> 21:38.987
please leave your name, number,

21:39.030 --> 21:41.089
and time of your call
after the beep.

21:41.130 --> 21:42.620
[ Beep ]

21:42.660 --> 21:44.298
HI.

21:44.330 --> 21:49.461
UH...IT'S STAN...BEEMAN.

21:49.500 --> 21:52.503
I'M CALLING FOR MATTHEW BEEMAN.

21:52.540 --> 21:55.270
IT'S DAD.

21:55.310 --> 21:57.949
I'M CALLING TO, UH...

21:57.980 --> 22:01.472
SAY HI AND GOOD NIGHT.

22:01.520 --> 22:04.842
SO...

22:04.890 --> 22:07.142
UH...

22:07.190 --> 22:09.852
YOU CAN CALL ME BACK
IF YOU GET A CHANCE

22:09.890 --> 22:13.997
OR...IF YOU GET IN...TONIGHT.

22:14.030 --> 22:17.056
IT'S, UH, 9:27.

22:19.570 --> 22:23.802
HI, SANDRA, ALSO.

22:23.840 --> 22:27.139
AND ARTHUR, I GUESS.

22:27.170 --> 22:29.604
OKAY. BYE.

22:44.590 --> 22:46.285
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

22:58.470 --> 22:59.732
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

23:06.580 --> 23:08.411
[ SIGHS ]

23:13.590 --> 23:14.887
HEY, STAN.

23:14.920 --> 23:17.627
I NEED TO SEE SANDRA.

23:18.930 --> 23:20.124
OF COURSE.

23:22.260 --> 23:25.923
I THOUGHT HE WAS GONNA
PULL THE TRIGGER. I REALLY DID.

23:25.970 --> 23:28.438
AND WHEN HE DIDN'T...

23:31.270 --> 23:34.273
I-I'M GLAD YOU'RE OKAY.

23:34.310 --> 23:37.131
BUT I'M NOT THE ONE
YOU SHOULD BE COMING TO.

23:37.180 --> 23:38.442
NO. I KNOW.

23:38.480 --> 23:40.402
I-I'M NOT ASKING YOU
FOR ANYTHING, SANDRA.

23:40.450 --> 23:41.474
I'M NOT FISHING.

23:41.520 --> 23:42.748
[ SIGHS ]

23:42.780 --> 23:44.179
THEN WHAT?

23:47.490 --> 23:49.788
YOU KNOW, AT EST, THEY SAID
THAT ALMOST GETTING KILLED

23:49.820 --> 23:52.288
IS ONE OF THOSE THINGS THAT
MAKES YOU FEEL REALLY ALIVE.

23:57.970 --> 23:59.995
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.

24:01.370 --> 24:04.237
I KNOW THAT I SHOULDN'T BE
COMING TO YOU ABOUT THIS --

24:04.270 --> 24:09.173
OR ABOUT...
ANYTHING, I GUESS.

24:11.680 --> 24:14.945
THE TRUTH IS...

24:14.980 --> 24:18.882
[Voice breaking ] YOU ARE
THE ONLY PERSON I WANT TO TELL.

24:25.160 --> 24:28.254
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

24:28.300 --> 24:30.154
WHY?

24:37.870 --> 24:39.565
I DON'T KNOW.

24:42.010 --> 24:43.329
[GULPS]

24:43.380 --> 24:47.305
I'M NOT COMING BACK
BECAUSE YOU ALMOST GOT SHOT.

24:47.350 --> 24:49.170
I KNOW.

24:50.720 --> 24:52.688
BUT I'M GLA--
I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE

24:52.720 --> 24:55.314
AND --
AND THAT YOU'RE...

24:55.360 --> 24:57.828
[Voice breaking ]
HOME AND SAFE.

24:57.860 --> 24:59.555
IAM.

25:00.730 --> 25:02.027
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

25:03.830 --> 25:06.025
THAT'S ALL. I'M...

25:08.170 --> 25:10.195
THAT'S ALL THERE IS.

25:13.070 --> 25:15.231
[ BOTH EXHALE SHARPLY ]

25:19.880 --> 25:21.871
[ WOMAN SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

25:29.390 --> 25:30.414
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

25:32.060 --> 25:33.186
[ RECORDER CLICKS ]

25:33.230 --> 25:35.289
[ CASSETTE CLATTERS ]

25:39.230 --> 25:42.563
I WAS, UM,
I WAS THINKING.

25:42.600 --> 25:46.400
YOU -- YOU COULD SEE HER --
YOUR MOTHER.

25:49.040 --> 25:51.042
IT IS ONE OF THE THINGS
WE'RE GOOD AT --

25:51.080 --> 25:52.775
GETTING PEOPLE
ACROSS BORDERS.

25:57.050 --> 26:00.247
AND THEY OWE YOU THAT.

26:01.460 --> 26:03.781
WE CAN'T GO BACK.

26:09.300 --> 26:11.291
[ DOOR OPENS ]

26:11.330 --> 26:14.037
[ SIGHS ]

26:14.070 --> 26:17.096
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS,
TELEPHONES RINGING ]

26:20.940 --> 26:23.079
SIR.
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

26:23.110 --> 26:26.273
BEFORE YOU SAY ANYTHING,
IT WAS DARK.

26:26.310 --> 26:28.870
WE BOTH SAW HER
FOR ABOUT HALF A SECOND

26:28.920 --> 26:30.979
BEFORE
SHE BASHED OUR FACES IN.

26:33.090 --> 26:35.251
YEAH, HARD TO MAKE
AN EXACT MATCH

26:35.290 --> 26:38.088
WITH ANY
OF OUR PREVIOUS ONES.

26:38.130 --> 26:40.587
THEY ARE GOOD
WITH THE DISGUISES.

26:40.630 --> 26:42.450
MM.

26:42.500 --> 26:44.127
YOU'RE LUCKY
TO BE ALIVE, SIR.

26:44.170 --> 26:45.728
[ SIGHS ]

26:45.770 --> 26:48.068
ANYTHING ON THE DOCUMENT
ADERHOLT GOT IN THE FIGHT?

26:48.100 --> 26:50.295
CIA SAYS THEY'RE PEOPLE
WHO WORK ON AFGHANISTAN.

26:50.340 --> 26:51.807
THAT'S ALL
THEY'LL TELL US.

26:51.840 --> 26:53.307
WELL, THAT'S HELPFUL.

26:53.340 --> 26:55.171
YEAH.

26:56.640 --> 26:58.073
OH, BEEMAN?

26:58.110 --> 26:59.839
DON'T LET --

26:59.880 --> 27:01.142
[ SIGHS ]

27:01.180 --> 27:03.171
...WHAT'S-HER-NAME
GET KILLED.

27:16.500 --> 27:18.422
SHE SAID
YOU WENT TO SEE HER.

27:18.470 --> 27:22.099
SHE'S VERY BEAUTIFUL,
YOUR MOTHER.

27:22.140 --> 27:23.698
SHE AGED WELL?

27:23.740 --> 27:26.038
YES. SHE DID.

27:26.070 --> 27:28.709
MM.

27:28.740 --> 27:31.948
SHE WAS ALWAYS
VERY SERIOUS.

27:31.980 --> 27:34.642
WELL, THAT GENERATION.

27:34.680 --> 27:35.977
MY GENERATION.

27:36.020 --> 27:39.342
EVERYBODY LOST EVERYTHING
IN THE WAR.

27:39.390 --> 27:41.051
I KNOW.

27:41.090 --> 27:44.127
MAYBE SHE'S A LITTLE HAPPIER NOW
BECAUSE HER DAUGHTER IS ALIVE

27:44.160 --> 27:48.051
AND SHE'S GRATEFUL SHE'S MAKING
A DIFFERENCE IN THE WORLD.

27:52.270 --> 27:54.488
YOU KNOW,
YOU AND PHILIP SEEM DIFFERENT

27:54.540 --> 27:57.464
THAN YOU WERE
WHEN I WAS HERE BEFORE.

27:57.500 --> 27:59.661
WE ARE.

27:59.710 --> 28:00.904
WELL, WE WERE.

28:00.940 --> 28:02.339
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

28:02.380 --> 28:04.541
THINGS ARE HARD WITH PAIGE.

28:04.580 --> 28:06.377
TELL ME.

28:08.080 --> 28:10.514
THE OTHER DAY,
SHE SAID SHE THOUGHT

28:10.550 --> 28:12.586
PHILIP WAS HAVING
AN AFFAIR.

28:12.620 --> 28:14.087
WELL,
IT'S ALL THE LATE NIGHTS.

28:14.120 --> 28:15.052
MM.

28:15.090 --> 28:16.910
BUT SHE TRUSTS YOU?

28:16.960 --> 28:18.359
I DON'T KNOW.

28:18.390 --> 28:21.257
SHE'S A TEENAGER...
IN THIS COUNTRY.

28:21.300 --> 28:23.427
MM.

28:25.430 --> 28:28.433
[ WHEELS ROLLING ]

28:33.740 --> 28:35.207
HELLO?

28:35.240 --> 28:37.538
E-EXCUSE ME.
CAN I ASK ONE --

28:37.580 --> 28:39.605
[ WHEELS ROLLING ]

28:41.280 --> 28:43.919
[ BREATH ES DEEPLY ]

29:10.980 --> 29:13.369
I...

29:13.410 --> 29:16.948
I DON'T KNOW
HOW LONG I WILL BE HERE.

29:16.980 --> 29:18.618
I DID NOT DO ANYTHING.

29:18.650 --> 29:22.450
I'M INNOCENT,
BUT I, UH...

29:22.490 --> 29:26.119
I DO NOT KNOW IF THE EMBASSY
KNOWS THAT I'M HERE, SO...

29:26.160 --> 29:29.789
THIS ISN'T A PRISON
FOR INNOCENT PEOPLE.

29:48.320 --> 29:50.345
[ KNOCKS ON DOOR]

29:52.150 --> 29:54.209
[ LOCK DISENGAGES ]

30:00.830 --> 30:03.458
SO, YOU'LL BE HERE.
I'LL BE HERE.

30:03.500 --> 30:04.967
YOUSAF WILL BE WAITING.

30:05.000 --> 30:07.093
WE DON'T KNOW
IF THEY'RE GONNA COME TOGETHER

30:07.130 --> 30:08.358
OR IN SEPARATE CARS.

30:08.400 --> 30:10.095
HOPEFULLY SEPARATE.
YEAH.

30:10.140 --> 30:12.836
I GET FACES AND AS MANY
LICENSE PLATES AS I CAN.

30:12.870 --> 30:14.303
OKAY.

30:14.340 --> 30:16.274
YOU'RE IN A BETTER POSITION
THAN I AM TO GET OUT,

30:16.310 --> 30:19.302
SO IF THERE IS TROUBLE,
I'LL STAY IN MY ROOM

30:19.350 --> 30:22.239
AND MEET YOU BACK HOME
IN A FEW HOURS.

30:30.860 --> 30:33.351
[ DOOR OPENS ]

30:33.390 --> 30:35.028
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

30:35.060 --> 30:37.995
Paige: HERE. THIS ONE'S
A LITTLE LESS DEPRESSING.

30:38.030 --> 30:40.225
OR...DEPRESSING
IN A DIFFERENT WAY.

30:40.270 --> 30:43.660
"THE GOVERNMENT IS CUTTING BACK
ON STUDENT AID TO MOST COLLEGES

30:43.700 --> 30:46.407
AND WANTS CORPORATIONS
TO MAKE UP THE DIFFERENCE."

30:46.440 --> 30:49.637
GREAT. I'LL PROBABLY END UP
AT PEPSI GEORGETOWN UNIVERSITY.

30:49.680 --> 30:50.829
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:50.880 --> 30:52.302
I'M GOING
TO COCA-COLA COLLEGE.

30:52.350 --> 30:54.375
SINCE WHEN
DO YOU READ THE NEWSPAPER?

30:54.420 --> 30:57.048
I...READ THE NEWSPAPER.

31:35.120 --> 31:36.485
ANYTHING?

31:39.930 --> 31:41.295
CHECKING.

31:48.100 --> 31:49.328
OKAY.

31:59.580 --> 32:02.117
[ GEARSHII-T CLICKS ]

32:19.170 --> 32:21.866
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

32:27.370 --> 32:29.031
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

32:56.500 --> 32:58.036
I'M ON THEM.

32:58.070 --> 32:59.435
NO. WAIT. WAIT.
WAIT!

32:59.470 --> 33:01.836
GOD DAMN IT.

33:19.690 --> 33:23.228
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

34:54.460 --> 34:56.451
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

35:05.800 --> 35:07.119
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

35:09.840 --> 35:11.307
DID YOU SEE ANYBODY?

35:11.340 --> 35:13.262
GRAY TORONADO,
BLUE FORD.

35:13.310 --> 35:15.608
BLUE FORD. YEAH. GREAT.
DAMN IT.

35:15.640 --> 35:17.779
WHAT HAPPENED TO BREAKING OFF
IF THINGS DIDN'T LOOK RIGHT?

35:17.810 --> 35:19.277
THEY'RE PROBABLY
JUST THE OTHER GUYS

35:19.310 --> 35:20.971
THAT YOUSAF'S
MEETING WITH.

35:21.010 --> 35:22.477
THEY DIDN'T LOOK LIKE THEY WERE
WATCHING THAT CAREFULLY,

35:22.520 --> 35:24.215
AND THEY WEREN'T RUNNING A ROUTE
TO THE BAR.

35:26.520 --> 35:27.942
SO, YOU'RE SAYING

35:27.990 --> 35:30.811
THE CIA OFFICERS
THAT WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE OF

35:30.860 --> 35:33.283
AREN'T NECESSARILY
LOOKING FOR US.

35:33.330 --> 35:35.924
I LOST THAT LIST OF NAMES ONCE.
I AM NOT BLOWING THIS CHANCE.

35:35.960 --> 35:37.791
AND WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO --
GO IN THERE?

35:37.830 --> 35:39.127
IT'S A BAR
FULL OF PEOPLE.

35:39.170 --> 35:40.660
YEAH, WE'LL GO IN
AND HAVE A DRINK.

35:42.170 --> 35:43.262
WE'LL LEAVE THE CARS HERE.
THEY'LL NEVER SEE THEM AGAIN.

35:43.300 --> 35:44.961
AS FAR AS
THEY'RE CONCERNED,

35:45.010 --> 35:46.500
THIS IS THEIR MEETING
ON THEIR TURF.

35:46.540 --> 35:48.531
EVEN YOUSAF DIDN'T KNOW
WHERE THEY WERE GOING.

35:57.020 --> 35:59.511
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

36:05.760 --> 36:08.194
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

36:09.560 --> 36:11.096
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

36:12.700 --> 36:13.860
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

36:13.900 --> 36:16.368
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

36:16.400 --> 36:19.039
[ SPORTING EVENT PLAYS ON TV ]

36:28.110 --> 36:30.249
HI.
WELCOME TO COOPERS.

36:30.280 --> 36:32.009
I'M JENNY.
WHAT CAN I GET YOU?

36:32.050 --> 36:33.187
WHAT BEERS YOU HAVE?

36:33.220 --> 36:34.915
BUD, BUD LIGHT, COORS,
COORS LIGHT,

36:34.960 --> 36:36.416
MILLER, MILLER LIGHT,

36:36.460 --> 36:38.678
NATTY LIGHT, MICHELOB LIGHT,
SIERRA NEVADA, PBR,

36:38.730 --> 36:40.220
ROLLING ROCK, STEVENS POINT,

36:40.260 --> 36:43.923
YUENGLING, LORD CHESTERFIELD,
GENESEE CREAM, SCHAEFER,

36:43.960 --> 36:45.666
NEW ALBION, HEINEKEN,
AND GUINNESS.

36:45.700 --> 36:47.167
TWO MILLERS, PLEASE.
THANK YOU.

36:47.200 --> 36:49.191
I'M GONNA GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

36:49.240 --> 36:51.231
[ SPORTING EVENT CONTINUES ]

36:56.110 --> 36:59.147
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

37:01.280 --> 37:02.440
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

37:08.050 --> 37:09.779
IT'S ALREADY OUT THERE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:09.820 --> 37:13.051
EVERY CENT OF YOUR MONEY GOES TO
THE MOST RELIGIOUS MUJAHIDEEN.

37:13.090 --> 37:15.695
IF YOU WANT TO SUPPORT
THE MORE MODERATE FACTIONS,

37:15.730 --> 37:17.391
YOU HAVE TO FIND
ANOTHER WAY.

37:17.430 --> 37:19.091
THAT WAY IS ME.

37:23.770 --> 37:25.601
MNH!

37:25.640 --> 37:28.006
I THINK
YOU NEED TO SEE A DENTIST.

37:30.410 --> 37:32.105
THEY'RE LOOKING
FOR SOMEBODY MY SIZE

37:32.150 --> 37:34.209
WHO GOT HER FACE
SLAMMED AGAINST A HOOD OF A CAR.

37:34.250 --> 37:35.649
IF THEY'RE THOROUGH,

37:35.680 --> 37:37.773
THEY'LL BE CHECKING DENTISTS
FOR THE NEXT MONTH.

37:39.320 --> 37:40.582
[ PATRONS CHEER ]

37:40.620 --> 37:42.053
Man: OH, WHAT A SHOT!

37:42.090 --> 37:43.910
[ SCATTERED APPLAUSE ]

37:43.960 --> 37:46.383
WE SHOULD DO THIS
MORE OI-TEN.

37:46.430 --> 37:48.921
Female reporter:
PRESIDENT REAGAN WENT TO THE
SOVIET EMBASSY IN WASHINGTON

37:48.960 --> 37:51.497
TODAY TO OFFER CONDOLENCES ON
THE DEATH OF LEONID BREZHNEV.

37:51.530 --> 37:53.088
IT WAS THE FIRST TIME

37:53.130 --> 37:55.439
THE PRESIDENT HAD VISITED
THAT EMBASSY.

37:55.470 --> 37:57.097
Male reporter:
THE PRESIDENT WAS GREETED

37:57.140 --> 37:59.734
BY VETERAN SOVIET AMBASSADOR
DOBRYNIN.

37:59.770 --> 38:02.102
MR. REAGAN SIGNED
THE BOOK OF CONDOLENCES,

38:02.140 --> 38:05.439
SAYING, "MY CONDOLENCES TO THE
FAMILY OF PRESIDENT BREZHNEV

38:05.480 --> 38:07.641
AND THE PEOPLE
OF THE SOVIET UNION."

38:31.140 --> 38:33.028
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

38:34.680 --> 38:37.729
[ REPORTER CONTINUES
INDISTINCTLY ]

38:43.250 --> 38:45.286
PRESIDENT REAGAN
WILL NOT ATTEND

38:45.320 --> 38:48.687
MR. BREZHNEV'S FUNERAL
IN MOSCOW ON MONDAY.

39:34.700 --> 39:36.998
[ METAL CLINKING ]

39:37.040 --> 39:38.667
[ WHIRRING ]

39:38.710 --> 39:42.601
SO, YOU'VE GOT "MEET THE PRESS"
ON SUNDAY MORNING, 9:00 AM.

39:42.640 --> 39:45.108
AND NEWSWEEK
TOMORROW AFTERNOON.

39:45.150 --> 39:46.549
YOU KNOW NEWSWEEK?

39:46.580 --> 39:50.346
OF COURSE.
CIRCULATION, 3 MILLION.

39:50.380 --> 39:52.018
AT MY INSTITUTE,

39:52.050 --> 39:54.382
WE STUDY ALL MAJOR AMERICAN
NEWSPAPERS, MAGAZINES.

39:54.420 --> 39:56.411
PRAVDA HAS CIRCULATION
11 MILLION,

39:56.460 --> 39:58.257
BUT IT'S
A DAILY NEWSPAPER.

40:01.660 --> 40:02.627
MM.

40:02.660 --> 40:04.025
I WAS THINKING --

40:04.060 --> 40:06.199
IF WE DON'T HAVE
ANY MORE APPOINTMENTS TODAY,

40:06.230 --> 40:09.393
IS IT POSSIBLE THAT WE CAN SEE
SOME OF THE SIGHTS HERE,

40:09.440 --> 40:12.762
LIKE LINCOLN MEMORIAL
OR WASHINGTON MONUMENT?

40:12.810 --> 40:15.529
I'M SORRY. THERE ARE
TOO MANY PEOPLE IN THOSE PLACES.

40:15.580 --> 40:18.276
WE CAN'T PROVIDE THE KIND
OF SECURITY THAT WE NEED TO.

40:18.310 --> 40:19.743
[ BUTTON CLICKS ]

40:19.780 --> 40:23.272
SO, YOU THINK
ALL THIS SECURITY IS NECESSARY?

40:23.320 --> 40:27.438
Y-YOU THINK KGB WILL TRY
TO KILL ME HERE, IN AMERICA?

40:29.360 --> 40:33.228
WE DON'T KNOW WHAT THEY
MIGHT DO, MS. PREOBRAZHEN--

40:33.260 --> 40:35.296
YOU CAN CALL ME ZINAIDA.

40:35.330 --> 40:36.399
OKAY.

40:36.430 --> 40:38.660
ZINAIDA.

40:43.000 --> 40:44.968
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

40:46.640 --> 40:48.676
[ LOCK DISENGAGES ]

41:05.890 --> 41:09.496
[ LOCK DISENGAGES ]

41:47.400 --> 41:48.890
[ SIGHS ]

41:55.610 --> 41:57.237
NYET.

43:05.450 --> 43:10.114
UH, DID BARB GIVE YOU
THE OCTOBER RECEIPTS?

43:10.150 --> 43:11.515
YEAH.

43:16.960 --> 43:18.689
THAN KS.

43:36.480 --> 43:40.143
THIS STU FF
WITH PAIGE...

43:40.180 --> 43:42.648
IT'S NOT GOING TO
JUST GO AWAY.

43:45.890 --> 43:47.517
I KNOW.

43:49.820 --> 43:52.983
WHEN THEY CAME TO ME...

43:54.630 --> 43:57.952
...I HAD A WEEK TO DECIDE.

43:58.000 --> 43:59.627
I WENT HOME.

43:59.670 --> 44:02.491
I WASN'T ALLOWED
TO TELL ANYBODY.

44:02.540 --> 44:03.859
I WAS 16.

44:05.640 --> 44:08.803
I TOOK MY MOTHER
OUT TO THE LOPATINSKY GARDENS.

44:08.840 --> 44:11.707
I WAS GONNA BREAK THE RULES,
BUT I WAS GONNA USE TRADECRAl-T.

44:16.680 --> 44:20.138
I TOLD HERIEVERYTHING.

44:20.190 --> 44:22.181
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

44:26.090 --> 44:29.719
SHE DIDN'T BLINK.

44:29.760 --> 44:33.560
SHE TOLD ME TO GO
AND SERVE MY COUNTRY.

44:36.570 --> 44:41.906
WHEN I WAS CALLED,
MY MOTHER DIDN'T HESITATE.

45:22.950 --> 45:26.010
-- Captions by VITAC --
